creditors and then immediately setting up in business again emerged as the
top priority for small businesses in a survey by the Forum of Private
Business.
Seventy-five per cent of respondents named rogue directors as their top
concern followed by late payment legislation, mentioned by 69 per cent, the
simplification of regulations (67 per cent), compensation for complying with
government red tape (62 per cent) and signed contracts with banks (62 per
cent).
