Mr Markku Tapio, deputy head of the industry department, said the government
wanted to receive reports from the financial institutions involved by late
spring.
Finland has already earmarked Neste, the oil and petrochemicals group, for
privatisation. The Finnish Communist Party, which has played an important
role in the country's history, yesterday decided to file for bankruptcy. It
is a victim of Finland's deep recession and of share investments gone bad,
Reuter reports.
